external_knowledge:
- "population that surpasses the national average" refers to states with a population greater than the average population of all states;
- "air that is somewhat breathable" refers to states with an air quality index greater than 50;
- "average prosperity" refers to the average GDP of states;
- "financially robust" refers to states with an average GDP greater than the average GDP of all states.

- "Low unemployment rates" refer to unemployment < 4.0%;
- "Relatively low Gini coefficient" refers to Gini < 0.5;
- "High average number of COVID-19 cases" refers to an average of more than 1,000 cases.

- "High smoking rate" refers to a smoking rate greater than 20%;
- "High health insurance rate" refers to a health insurance rate greater than 90%;
- "Significant number of COVID-19 cases" refers to more than 10,000 new cases reported in total;
- "Did not close schools early" means the schools did not close before March 16, 2020, due to a COVID-19 outbreak.

- "the air is the most polluted" refers to the state with the highest average pollution level;
- "the soil is the most fertile with COVID-19 cases" refers to the state with the highest total number of COVID-19 cases;
- "the maturest population" refers to the state with the highest median age;
- "the densest people" refers to the state with the highest population density.

